fields.description:
*Summary*

As a plan admin I do not have permission to view an issue source and when viewing issue sources I see "No Permission to access source" 

It would be better if this showed the ID of the source that I am not able to view. This way I can find out who owns the source and obtain permission. 

*Workaround:* 
* View the source of the page (right click on page, "View Page Source")
* Search for "jpo-wr-page-plan-setup-planinfo.com.atlassian.jpo.basicplaninfo"
** The area after this contains the list of sources. Below is an example: 

{noformat}
WRM._unparsedData["com.atlassian.jpo:jpo-wr-page-plan-setup-planinfo.com.atlassian.jpo.basicplaninfo"]="{\"plan\":{\"id\":1,\"title\":\"Travel Booking Division (Live Plan)\",\"planningUnit\":\"StoryPoints\",\"issueSources\":[{\"id\":1,\"sprintIds\":[],\"type\":\"Board\",\"value\":\"6\",\"title\":\"Platform Development\"},{\"id\":2,\"sprintIds\":[9,10],\"type\":\"Board\",\"value\":\"7\",\"title\":\"IOS app\"},{\"id\":3,\"sprintIds\":[],\"type\":\"Board\",\"value\":\"8\",\"title\":\"Android App Development\"},{\"id\":4,\"sprintIds\":[2],\"type\":\"Board\",\"value\":\"9\",\"title\":\"Performance Engineering\"},{\"id\":5,\"sprintIds\":[],\"type\":\"Board\",\"value\":\"10\",\"title\":\"Portfolio Management\"},{\"id\":6,\"sprintIds\":[],\"type\":\"Board\",\"value\":\"11\",\"title\":\"Team Travel Web\"},{\"id\":7,\"sprintIds\":[],\"type\":\"Filter\",\"value\":\"10300\",\"title\":\"Alana: Deals and Offers\"}],\"excludedVersions\":[]}}";
{noformat}

You will not see a "title" if you do not have permission. You will still see the ID of the source. The ID shows as the "value" for example {{\"type\":\"Filter\",\"value\":\"10300\"}}

Environment
 OS Ubuntu Server 16.04, Jira Software 7.1.10 , jdk 1.8.0_171-b11, Portfolio 2.13.1
 OS Windows 10, Jira Software 7.10.1, jdk 1.8.0_172, Portfolio 2.13.3

Steps to Reproduce
 * Start Jira and add the Due date, Target Start (e.g. customfield_10109), Target End (e.g. customfield_1011) fields to the create issue screen (e.g. for Epics)
 * Shutdown Jira
 * Set the timezone of the OS to UTC
 * Start Jira
 * Create an Epic using the rest interface of jira [http://SERVER/rest/api/2/issue|http://server/rest/api/2/issue] (POST)
{code:java}
{
   "fields":{
      "project":{
         "key":"TP"
      },
      "issuetype":{
         "name":"Epic"
      },
      "summary":"Some Epic",
      "duedate":"2018-03-03",
      "customfield_10104":"Some Epic",
      "customfield_10109":"2018-02-02",
      "customfield_10110":"2018-03-03"
   }
}
{code}

 * Issue will have the following values:
 ** Target start 2018-02-02
 ** Target end 2018-03-03
 ** Due date 2018-03-03
 * Shutdown Jira
 * Set the timezone of the OS to CEST
 * Start Jira
 * Create an Epic using the rest interface of jira [http://SERVER/rest/api/2/issue|http://server/rest/api/2/issue] (POST)
{code:java}
{
   "fields":{
      "project":{
         "key":"TP"
      },
      "issuetype":{
         "name":"Epic"
      },
      "summary":"Some Epic",
      "duedate":"2018-03-03",
      "customfield_10104":"Some Epic",
      "customfield_10109":"2018-02-02",
      "customfield_10110":"2018-03-03"
   }
}
{code}

 * Issue will have the following values:
 ** Target start 2018-02-01
 ** Target end 2018-03-02
 ** Due date 2018-03-03

Expected Results
 The time zone of the operating system should not cause any problems.

Actual Results
 One day is deducted from the Target start / Target end fields.

The suggest Rest Service (/rest/jpo/1.0/parent/suggest) needs the following json as payload:
{code}
{"query":"","issueTypeName":"Epic","maxResults":100}
{code}

Jira's Rest-services return the issue type name in the user's language (changed within: https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRASERVER-27113)

If you use the German issue type name, 
{code}
{"query":"","issueTypeName":"Episch","maxResults":100}
{code}
no results will come back.

The suggest Rest Service does not use the user's language. It uses internally, probably, the default language of the jira system.

The service should:
first search with the default language and then with the language of the user.
or
you should be able to use the issue type id.
{code}
{"query":"","issueTypeId":5,"maxResults":100}
{code}
